drug.name: Fenoterol
drug.description: Fenoterol is an adrenergic beta-2 agonist that is used as a bronchodilator and tocolytic.
drug.synthesis-reference: Zeile, K., Thoma, O. and Mentrup, A,; U.S. Patent 3,341,593; September 12, 1967; assigned to Boehringer lngelheim GmbH, Germany.
drug.indication: Fenoterol is used for the treatment of asthma.
drug.pharmacodynamics: Fenoterol is a beta agonist designed to open up the airways to the lungs by decreasing bronchconstriction.
drug.mechanism-of-action: Beta(2)-receptor stimulation in the lung causes relaxation of bronchial smooth muscle, bronchodilation, and increased bronchial airflow.
drug.toxicity: Symptoms of overdose include angina (chest pain), dizziness, dry mouth, fatigue, flu-like symptoms, headache, heart irregularities, high or low blood pressure, high blood sugar, insomnia, muscle cramps, nausea, nervousness, rapid heartbeat, seizures, and tremor.

classification.description: This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as amphetamines and derivatives. These are organic compounds containing or derived from 1-phenylpropan-2-amine.
